Description: Fragment of neck and flattened handle of Koan pottery transport amphora, gradual curve. Clay fine cream-buff; some mica. Rectangular stamp with Greek inscription.
Curator's comments: Name Zenodotos For the name on Koan double handles see G. Jöhrens, Amphorenstempel aus den Grabungen in Milet 1899-2007, AA 2009 205-235, no. 38. Trimmed.
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (JB.0181)
